PROJECT CASE STUDY: Delivery Performance & DPMO Tracker
Developer: Ben Julius
Platform: Amazon Mercury (Internal Dashboard & Reporting Engine)
Project Overview
This project was developed to address a critical visibility gap in Last-Mile delivery operations.
This custom-built Mercury dashboard provides real-time, high-definition tracking of undelivered
packages, calculates the Defects Per Million Opportunities (DPMO) dynamically, and
categorizes delivery failures to drive operational improvements.
The Problem
Lack of Real-Time KPI Tracking: Leadership and Shift Assistants lacked a centralized, real-time
view of daily delivery health and DPMO metrics.
No Centralized Root-Cause Analysis: When packages were missed, digging into the "why" (e.g.,
vehicle breakdowns, customer-unreachable, bad addresses) required manually pulling and
cross-referencing multiple data sources, delaying course corrections during active shifts.
The Solution
I built a real-time tracking dashboard utilizing Amazon's internal Mercury platform to ingest,
process, and visualize delivery success metrics.
Dynamic DPMO Calculation: Automatically calculates delivery quality metrics. For example, if
1,000 packages are scheduled and 990 are successfully delivered, the dashboard dynamically
calculates and displays a DPMO of 10,000.
Granular Failure Breakdown: Features a drill-down data table listing every single missed
package, mapping it to the assigned route, driver, and specific standard failure code.
Visual Pareto Charting: Categorizes delivery failures (e.g., Access Issue, Business Closed,
Package Damaged) to visually show operations teams exactly where to focus their recovery
efforts.
System Architecture & Data Flow
[Raw Delivery Data Stream] ──► Ingests live logistics data.
[Mercury Engine] ──► Processes custom query logic and filtering.
[Aggregation Layer] ──► Calculates DPMO: (Defects / Opportunities) * 1,000,000.
[Dashboard UI] ──► Displays KPI cards, Pareto breakdowns, and the active defect log.
Business Impact & KPIs
Improved Shift Response: Reduced the time to identify and action failing routes from hours to
minutes, allowing for mid-shift package rescues.
Targeted Feedback: Provided Process Assistants and Managers with clear, driver-level data to
address recurring delivery issues.
Precision Quality Tracking: Transitioned the site from relying on basic percentage metrics to
utilizing industry-standard DPMO, enabling highly precise quality control.